   MEDIA ADVISORY June 8, 2001 Contact: Curtis Carey (301) 713-0622 Robert
   Chartuk (631) 244-0166 NOAA and PGA Tours' Rocco Mediate Spotlight
   Leading Weather Killer  Lightning Tuesday, June 19, 2001 2:00 p.m.
   Buick Classic Golf Tournament Westchester Country Club Harrison, N.Y.
   The National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's (NOAA) National
   Weather Service (NWS) and PGA TOUR professional Rocco Mediate will
   unveil a nationwide public awareness campaign about the dangers of
   lightning at a press conference during the Buick Classic golf
   tournament. The campaign features a television public service
   announcement starring Mediate, posters on lightning safety, and a
   national lightning safety Web page. BACKGROUND INFORMATION: On average,
   lightning strikes in America kill 73 people a year, more than tornadoes
   or hurricanes. Further information is found on the new lightning
   awareness Web site: http://www.lightningsafety.noaa.gov. INTERVIEWS:
   Scott B. Gudes, NOAA's acting administrator Rocco Mediate, PGA TOUR
   professional golfer Dr. May Ann Cooper, expert on lightning victim
   recovery Michael Utley, lightning strike survivor NOTE TO MEDIA: The
   PSA and B-roll footage of lightning will be available in Beta-SP format
   at the press conference. - 30 -
